modules.description: Generates random boolean decision diagrams using a configurable probability distribution for node creation and variable selection. Operates on abstract syntax trees representing logical expressions and binary decision diagrams. Used to test SAT solvers and evaluate the performance of BDD manipulation algorithms under varying structural complexity.

Parses a DIMACS formatted string into a structured representation, and converts it back to a string. It processes clauses and variables, extracting variable lists and logical formulas. Used to interface with SAT solvers by transforming input and output between textual and internal formats.

Generates variable assignments based on Boolean and numeric constraints using a randomization engine. Operates on lists of Boolean and numeric variables, along with logical formulas or DIMACS files specifying constraints. Used to create randomized test cases that satisfy given logical conditions.
